<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="367" pageId="2" pageNumber="365" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1590,2013]" pageId="2" pageNumber="365">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1662,1688]" pageId="2" pageNumber="365">Description.</emphasis>
Length 
<quantity box="[445,586,1663,1689]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.75" metricValueMax="3.9" metricValueMin="3.6" pageId="2" pageNumber="365" unit="mm" value="3.75" valueMax="3.9" valueMin="3.6">3.6–3.9 mm</quantity>
; width 
<quantity box="[675,816,1663,1689]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.35" metricValueMax="1.4" metricValueMin="1.3" pageId="2" pageNumber="365" unit="mm" value="1.35" valueMax="1.4" valueMin="1.3">1.3–1.4 mm</quantity>
. Body elongate, covered with large nearly coalescing punctures bearing setae, surface structure and setae can obscure other characters (
<figureCitation box="[1056,1163,1699,1725]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1900,1924]" captionTargetBox="[191,1392,442,1836]" captionTargetId="figure-103@3.[151,1436,417,1876]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. Echinothallis banderbearella sp. nov.: 1–3) habitus, holotype; 1) dorsal view; 2) ventral view; 3) lateral view; 4) female genitalia, allotype; 5–8) male genitalia, paratype; 5) abdominal segments VIII–IX, ventral view; 6) tegmen, dorsal view; 7) penis, lateral view; 8) penis, dorsal view. Scale bars: 1–3 = 1.0 mm, 4–8 = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4629080" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4629080/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="365">Figs. 1–3</figureCitation>
); setae variable between two forms, long dark erect bristles, shorter golden recumbent setae; body color entirely dark brown, appendages slightly lighter.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1590,2013]" pageId="2" pageNumber="365">Head with surface entirely covered by deep setose punctures same diameter as facets; dorsal interocular distance = 4× eye; fronto-clypeal suture obscured in surface structure.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1590,2013]" lastBlockId="3.[151,1437,151,393]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="366" pageId="2" pageNumber="365">Antenna relatively long, slender, club strong moderately tight; antennomere 1 large, width 1.5× width of antennomere 2; antennomere 2 circular; antennomere 3 elongate, 2× longer than antennomere 2; antennomeres 2–7 nearly equal in width; antennomeres 4–7 as wide as long; antennomere 8 as long as antennomere 7, 1.2× wider than antennomere 7, apically angled at sides; antennomeres 9–10 1.5× longer and 1.5× wider than antennomere 7, subtrapezoidal, apex flat; antennomere 11 transversely elliptical, width slightly less than antennomere 10, apically obliquely truncate.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,151,393]" pageId="3" pageNumber="366">Pronotum convex, sides at anterior 1/3, almost quadrate, width = 1.1× length at midline; entire discal surface densely covered with coarse deep, seta bearing punctures that nearly coalesce.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,151,393]" pageId="3" pageNumber="366">Elytra with striae evident, punctures seta bearing, as large as pronotal punctures, nearly touching next puncture in row, not reduced laterally; intervals with smaller setae bearing punctures; surface smooth; epipleuron moderately wide basally, evenly narrowing to apex, with small seta bearing punctures.</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4629080" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4629080" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4629080/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="366" startId="3.[151,264,1900,1924]" targetBox="[191,1392,442,1836]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1900,1996]" pageId="3" pageNumber="366">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,314,1900,1924]" pageId="3" pageNumber="366">FIGURES 1–8.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Skelley &amp; Leschen &amp; Liu, 2021" authorityName="Skelley &amp; Leschen &amp; Liu" authorityYear="2021" box="[321,617,1900,1924]" class="Insecta" family="Erotylidae" genus="Echinothallis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="366" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="banderbearella" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[321,617,1900,1924]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="366">Echinothallis banderbearella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[624,704,1900,1924]" pageId="3" pageNumber="366">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[624,704,1900,1924]" pageId="3" pageNumber="366" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
: 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[718,765,1900,1924]" pageId="3" pageNumber="366">1–3)</emphasis>
habitus, holotype; 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[958,980,1900,1924]" pageId="3" pageNumber="366">1)</emphasis>
dorsal view; 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1116,1138,1900,1924]" pageId="3" pageNumber="366">2)</emphasis>
ventral view; 
